# Dispatcher (always-on routing)

- **Role**: Recognize **queue-related** triggers and route them to the **Queue/Dispatcher subagent**. All other triggers (INGEST_MODE, DISTILL_MODE, EXPRESS_MODE, ARCHIVE_MODE, ORGANIZE_MODE, roadmap modes, GARDEN REVIEW, CURATE CLUSTER, etc.) continue to map to their existing context rules as documented in [system-funnels.mdc](.cursor/rules/always/system-funnels.mdc).
- **Shared core**: Every run must still apply the shared always rules: [core-guardrails.mdc](.cursor/rules/always/core-guardrails.mdc), [confidence-loops.mdc](.cursor/rules/always/confidence-loops.mdc), [guidance-aware.mdc](.cursor/rules/always/guidance-aware.mdc), [mcp-obsidian-integration.mdc](.cursor/rules/always/mcp-obsidian-integration.mdc), [watcher-result-append.mdc](.cursor/rules/always/watcher-result-append.mdc), [backbone-docs-sync.mdc](.cursor/rules/always/backbone-docs-sync.mdc). This rule does not replace them; it only adds routing for the triggers below.

## Delegation and fallback

- **Dispatch via Task subagent tool (with Task harden pass)**: For pipeline modes (ingest, roadmap, distill, express, archive, organize, research, **validator**), the queue processor **never calls the raw Task tool directly**. Instead, it MUST invoke the **Task harden pass** described in [[3-Resources/Second-Brain/Subagent-Safety-Contract|Subagent-Safety-Contract]] § **Task harden pass (capability probing, profiles, and launch modes)**:
  - Pass **prompt** = the full hand-off block (per Subagent-Safety-Contract) and **desired_subagent_type** = the pipeline type (roadmap | ingest | distill | express | archive | organize | research | validator), along with the current **task_role** (e.g. `layer1_queue`) and **effective_pipeline_mode** / profile snapshot from Config.
  - The harden pass:
    - Uses the **per-run capability cache** (`available_subagents` / `raw_errors`) to decide whether this `subagent_type` is actually supported by the host.
    - Applies the **profile-specific helper graph** (fast | balance | extreme) to decide whether this helper is **mandatory** or **out of graph** for this run.
    - Normalizes the launch decision:
      - `launch_mode: native_subagent` when `available_subagents[type] === true`.
      - `launch_mode: generalPurpose_fallback` only for non-mandatory helpers when explicitly configured.
      - Or marks the step as **blocked** (no Task call) when a **mandatory** helper is unavailable, so the parent MUST NOT report full Success.
  - When the harden pass elects to launch, it calls the Cursor `Task` tool on behalf of this rule with the chosen `subagent_type` and a decorated prompt that includes:
    - `task_harden_metadata.layer_role: layer1_queue`,
    - `task_harden_metadata.launch_mode: native_subagent | generalPurpose_fallback`,
    - `task_harden_metadata.expected_contract` identifying the contract (e.g. `roadmap_handoff_auto`, `archive_candidate`, etc.).
  - For **ROADMAP_HANDOFF_VALIDATE**, the queue passes **model** from Config § validator.roadmap_handoff.model into the harden pass so the underlying `Task(validator)` call uses the fixed model when it is actually reachable.
  - The subagent still runs in a separate context with only that prompt; the queue processor waits for the Task call to return, inspects the child’s `task_harden_result` footer (`task_launch_mode`, `contract_satisfied`) when present, logs Watcher-Result, and continues. When `contract_satisfied: false` on a **mandatory** contract under the active profile, Layer 1 MUST NOT treat the entry as fully successful even if the subagent text claims “Success”.
  - Pipeline subagents may in turn call only the three sanctioned **nested helper** subagents defined in the Subagent-Safety-Contract — **Internal Repair Agent (IRA)**, **Validator**, and **Research** — and must route those nested calls through the **same Task harden pass** (task_role `helper_internal_repair_agent` / `helper_validator` / `helper_research`) instead of using raw Task.
  - **PromptCraftSubagent** is **not** a nested pipeline helper: **only Layer 0 (manual)** or **Layer 1 ([[.cursor/rules/agents/queue.mdc|queue.mdc]] A.5d)** may call **`Task(prompt_craft)`** (again via the Task harden pass with `desired_subagent_type: "prompt_craft"`); IRA and Validator must **never** call it.
- **Task `model` (Cursor API):** **Omit** `model` on Task calls to use the parent chat's model (inherit behavior). Use **`model: "fast"`** only when intentionally selecting the fast tier. **Never** pass `model: "inherit"` — invalid and fails validation. Validator (and similar) dispatches pass Config `model` as documented. Agent files `.cursor/agents/*.md` may use YAML `model: inherit`; that is **not** a Task payload value. See [Subagent-Safety-Contract](3-Resources/Second-Brain/Subagent-Safety-Contract.md) § Cursor Task tool: `model` parameter.
- **All pipeline dispatch via subagent**: All pipeline-mode entries **must** be routed through the **Task** subagent tool (launch explicit subagent). There is **no same-run fallback**. If a Task call **fails**, do **not** run the pipeline inline. For that entry: append a failure line to Watcher-Result (requestId, status: failure, message e.g. "subagent launch required; Task subagent call failed"), log to Errors.md per Error Handling Protocol, do not add the entry to processed_success_ids (so it remains in the queue or is marked queue_failed at rewrite), and continue to the next entry.
- **Watcher-Result**: If the agent cannot write to `3-Resources/Watcher-Result.md` (permission or sandbox), it logs the intended line to `3-Resources/Errors.md` (Watcher-Result fallback) and continues; queue completion is not blocked.
- **Rollback / legacy mode:** Production no longer supports inline pipeline execution. To disable native subagents while keeping legacy rules for reference, rename or remove `.cursor/agents/*.md`; pipeline dispatch still requires the **Task** subagent tool (no same-run fallback). Deprecated fallback behavior is documented in [[4-Archives/Resources/Second-Brain-Deprecated/Queue-Same-Run-Fallback-2026-03-17]].

## Queue triggers → spawn Layer 1 (Queue subagent) via Task

When the user instruction contains any of these (case-insensitive):

- **EAT-QUEUE** *(canonical)* — includes **EAT-QUEUE BREAK-SPIN** (same queue pass; see **BREAK-SPIN** below)
- **Process queue**
- **EAT-CACHE** / **eat cache**
- **PROCESS TASK QUEUE**

then **Layer 0 (this agent) must NOT run queue logic**. Your **only** action is to **launch the Queue/Dispatcher subagent (Layer 1)** by **calling the `Task` tool once**. Per [[3-Resources/Second-Brain/Subagent-Safety-Contract|Subagent-Safety-Contract]] § Task-`attempt-before-skip`, you **must attempt** this Task call with `subagent_type: "queue"` rather than inferring from schema that it is unavailable; treat only real Task errors as unavailability.

1. **Build a hand-off** for the Queue subagent that includes:
   - Vault root (workspace path).
   - Prompt queue path: `.technical/prompt-queue.jsonl`.
   - Task queue path: `3-Resources/Task-Queue.md`.
   - Which to process: prompt queue (EAT-QUEUE / Process queue / EAT-CACHE) or task queue (PROCESS TASK QUEUE) or both if the user asked for both.
   - If EAT-CACHE with pasted payload: include the pasted payload (e.g. `queued_prompts`) in the hand-off.
   - **BREAK-SPIN (optional):** When the instruction contains **BREAK-SPIN** (with **EAT-QUEUE** / **Process queue**), include any **operator-authored** YAML from the user message in the hand-off as a dedicated section **`## operator_break_spin`** with a fenced **`yaml`** block. Minimal schema (all keys optional except intent): **`operator_break_spin: true`**, **`break_spin_target_queue_entry_id`**, **`break_spin_preferred_action`** (`deepen` \| `recal` \| …), **`break_spin_pivot_to_track`**, **`break_spin_rationale`**, **`break_spin_circled_locus`**. Layer 1 merges this into **`layer1_resolver_hints`** / roadmap hand-off per [[.cursor/rules/agents/queue.mdc|queue.mdc]] (alternate deepen first; **recal** only as fallback when no alternates or operator override — not the default “break” from spin).
   - Instruction: "You are the Queue/Dispatcher subagent (Layer 1). Process the queue(s) as specified in .cursor/rules/agents/queue.mdc: Step 0 (wrappers), read, parse/validate/dedup/order, then for each pipeline entry call the Task tool to launch that pipeline's subagent, Watcher-Result, rewrite. Do not run queue logic in the parent context; you run in this context only."
2. **Task hand-off comms (Layer 0→1):** When Second-Brain-Config **`task_handoff_comms.enabled`** is not **false**, **before** **`Task`**: read-append-write **`.technical/task-handoff-comms.jsonl`** with **`handoff_out`** per [[3-Resources/Second-Brain/Docs/Task-Handoff-Comms-Spec|Task-Handoff-Comms-Spec]] — new **`task_correlation_id`** (UUID), **`parent_task_correlation_id`: null**, **`from_actor: layer0_chat`**, **`to_actor: layer1_queue`**, **`subagent_type: queue`**, **`queue_entry_id`**: `"-"` or synthetic id if known, **`parent_run_id`**, **`project_id`**, **`vault_root`**, **`body`** = full **`prompt`** for the Queue **`Task`** (sanitized), **`sanitization_rules_applied`**. **After** **`Task`** returns, append **`return_in`** with the same **`task_correlation_id`** and full return or sanitized error. Respect **`task_handoff_comms.max_body_bytes`**.
3. **Call the `Task` tool** with **subagent_type: `queue`** (or the type that loads `.cursor/agents/queue.md`), **description**: one sentence (e.g. "Process the prompt queue and/or task queue"), **prompt**: the full hand-off text above. Wait for the Task call to return.
4. **Do not** read `.technical/prompt-queue.jsonl` or `3-Resources/Task-Queue.md` yourself. **Do not** run Step 0, parse, dispatch, or Watcher-Result in this context. If the Task tool is unavailable or the call fails, report that the Queue subagent could not be launched and do not run queue steps inline.
5. **Layer 0 loud wrap (optional; after `Task(queue)` returns only):** When Second-Brain-Config **`queue.layer0_escalation_enabled`** is **true**, parse the Queue subagent **return** text for a fenced **`yaml`** block under **`## layer0_queue_signals`** (see [[.cursor/agents/queue.md|agents/queue.md]]). If **`no_gain_terminal`** or **`break_spin_zero_alternates`** is **true**, prepend **one or more** lines from **`queue.layer0_no_gain_voice_lines`** (or the vault path **`queue.layer0_no_gain_voice_vault_path`** when set) to **your user-visible reply** — blunt / attention-grabbing copy is allowed **here only**. **Do not** put loud copy in **`3-Resources/Watcher-Result.md`** `message` or in subagent returns; keep Watcher lines **neutral and parse-safe** per [[.cursor/rules/always/watcher-result-append.mdc|watcher-result-append]].

## PromptCraft triggers (Layer 0 — not EAT-QUEUE)

When the user instruction contains **REPAIR CRAFT** or **PROMPT CRAFT RECOVERY** (case-insensitive), **Layer 0** does **not** run queue logic. **Layer 0** builds a hand-off from the user message (paste **`prompt_craft_request`** YAML if supplied, or describe failure context) and **calls the `Task` tool** once with **subagent_type `prompt_craft`** (or **generalPurpose** + PromptCraft preamble if the host enum lacks `prompt_craft`). **Layer 0 does not append** `.technical/prompt-queue.jsonl`; the operator or a subsequent EAT-QUEUE / Layer 1 step applies lines. See [[3-Resources/Second-Brain/Docs/Prompt-Craft-Subagent|Prompt-Craft-Subagent]]. When **`task_handoff_comms.enabled`** is not **false**, wrap that **`Task`** with **`handoff_out` / `return_in`** appends to **`.technical/task-handoff-comms.jsonl`** per [[3-Resources/Second-Brain/Docs/Task-Handoff-Comms-Spec|Task-Handoff-Comms-Spec]] (**`from_actor: layer0_chat`**, **`parent_task_correlation_id`: null**, fresh **`task_correlation_id`** per call).

## Other triggers

All other mode phrases (INGEST_MODE, DISTILL_MODE, EXPRESS_MODE, ARCHIVE_MODE, ORGANIZE_MODE, ROADMAP_MODE, RESUME_ROADMAP, GARDEN REVIEW, CURATE CLUSTER, etc.) are **not** handled by this dispatcher; they continue to be routed per [system-funnels.mdc](.cursor/rules/always/system-funnels.mdc). For pipeline modes (ingest, distill, express, archive, organize, roadmap, research, validator): queue processor **calls the Task tool** with hand-off as prompt and matching subagent_type (validator for ROADMAP_HANDOFF_VALIDATE; model from config when applicable). Direct triggers (user said "Resume roadmap" etc. without EAT-QUEUE): route through the **Task** tool with hand-off + subagent_type only; if the Task tool is unavailable, report that subagent launch is required. *(Deprecated same-run fallback archived: [[4-Archives/Resources/Second-Brain-Deprecated/Queue-Same-Run-Fallback-2026-03-17]].)*
